      <notes>Biography History: Born in Ahmednagar, India, the son of a Christian missionary, Henry Ballantine graduated from Amherst College in 1868 then returned to India where he was a merchant in Bombay from 1870-1872. Ballantine traveled to the Himalayas and Nepal in 1885 and 1888, and he also served as U.S. Consul to India from 1891-1896. During this time, he collected and took photographs and wrote about his travels in a book, On India's frontier, or, Nepal, the Ghurkas' mysterious land (1896).</notes>
